pleasant /ˈplɛzənt/

(pleasanter,pleasantest) 

1. ADJ Something that is pleasant is nice, enjoyable, or attractive. 令人愉快的 

例： I've got a pleasant little apartment. 我有一套舒适的小公寓。 

2. pleasantly ADV 令人愉快地 

例： We talked pleasantly of old times. 我们愉快地谈论着过去的时光。 

3. ADJ Someone who is pleasant is friendly and likeable. 友善的 

例： The woman had a pleasant face. 那个女人长着一张和善的脸。

